# Security Reviewer (reminder)

When editing these files, keep security in mind. For a full vulnerability review, invoke the **security-reviewer** subagent.

## Quick checklist

- **Route Handlers (`app/api/**`):** Validate all inputs; avoid command injection and path traversal; limit payload sizes where relevant; no secrets in responses or logs; correct authz if endpoints are non-public.
- **Backend (Go, when present):** Parameterized queries only; no secrets in code or logs; validate and sanitize input; auth checks on protected routes; secure session/token handling.
- **Frontend / Next:** No secrets in client bundles; never trust raw user HTML without sanitization; prefer httpOnly cookies for session tokens when applicable; avoid sensitive data in URLs or `localStorage` when avoidable.
- **Config:** Secrets only in env; `.env.local` / `.env` not committed; `.env.example` documents variables without real values.

For a dedicated security pass, ask the main agent to delegate to **security-reviewer**.
